date
time
uptime
cd --> change directory
/ --> root
ls --> list all the files/directories
ls -lrt --> list all the files/directories by time
mkdir --> crete a directory
touch --> create a file
vi --> i --> edit the file --> esc (exit insert mode) --> :wq!
clear --> clear the screen
cat --> read a file
rmdir
rm
chmod --> permissions

Linux distributions:
CentOS - Amazon Linux, Redhat, Fedora - yum is the default package manager
Debian - Ubuntu - apt is the default package manager
